      • strictParse

        public T strictParse(String string)
              throws ParseException
        Unambiguous string parser. Strings will be parsed as the given data types if and only if the following conditions are met, with surrounding whitespace ignored in each case:
        • BINARY: 0x#
        • STRING: any string with normal escaping rules, surrounded by the following character at each end, ignoring quotes: "'"
        • INTEGER: #I
        • DECIMAL: #D
        • INT: #i
        • LONG: #l
        • FLOAT: #f
        • DOUBLE: #d
        • BOOLEAN: true|false
        • QUALIFIED_NAME: @[Qualified Name]
        Parameters:
        string -
        Returns:
        Throws:
        ParseException
